sentences: Orpheo McCord (born 1979) is an American composer and percussionist.
He is an original member of Edward Sharpe and the Magnetic Zeros, and a former member of The Fall, Fool's Gold and Cass McCombs.
His debut solo album, Recovery Inhale, was released on January 26, 2018.
McCord attended Berklee College of Music, graduating in 2002.
The Fall (2006-07)
The Fall (2006-07)
In May 2006 after several members of U.K. Band The Fall quit mid-tour, McCord was recruited by frontman Mark E. Smith to join The Fall along with guitarist Tim Presley and bassist Rob Barbato.
